title: Peschanokopskoye
summary: Peschanokopskoye (Russian: Песчанокопское) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Peschanokopsky District in Rostov Oblast, Russia. Population: 10,593 (2010 Census); 11,357 (2002 Census); 10,966 (1989 Census).
content:
Peschanokopskoye (Russian: Песчанокопское) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Peschanokopsky District in Rostov Oblast, Russia. Population: 10,593 (2010 Census); 11,357 (2002 Census); 10,966 (1989 Census).
